<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-05-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-05-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="619" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d619">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.162/74: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-05-24T13:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">May 24,
                                        1926—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:25
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>68. Speaker of the National Assembly has just informed me that the
                            Deputies are opposed to ratification of the treaty before the United
                            States Senate ratifies it. As the Assembly adjourns in one week till
                            February prompt action necessary.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>